Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: ## Step 1
To determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$, we first need to understand what $Y_7$ represents. $Y_7$ is the 7th order statistic out of 8 independent observations from a given distribution. This means it is the 7th smallest value when the observations are arranged in ascending order.

## Step 2
The given distribution has a 70th percentile, $\pi_{0.7}$, equal to 27.3. This implies that the probability of any single observation being less than 27.3 is 0.7, because $\pi_{0.7}$ is the value below which 70% of the observations fall.

## Step 3
To calculate $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$, we need to consider the probability that at least 7 out of the 8 observations are less than 27.3. This can be approached using the binomial probability formula, where the number of trials $n = 8$, the probability of success $p = 0.7$ (since success here is defined as an observation being less than 27.3), and we are interested in the probability of 7 or 8 successes.

## Step 4
The probability of exactly $k$ successes in $n$ trials is given by the binomial probability formula: $P(X = k) = \binom{n}{k} p^k (1-p)^{n-k}$. We need to calculate $P(X = 7)$ and $P(X = 8)$ and sum them to find $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.

## Step 5
Calculate $P(X = 7)$: $\binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (1-0.7)^{8-7} = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times (0.3)^1$.
$P(X = 7) = 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 8 \times 0.02470629 = 0.19765032$.

## Step 6
Calculate $P(X = 8)$: $\binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 (1-0.7)^{8-8} = 1 \times (0.7)^8 \times (0.3)^0$.
$P(X = 8) = 1 \times 0.05764801 \times 1 = 0.05764801$.

## Step 7
Sum $P(X = 7)$ and $P(X = 8)$ to find $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$: $0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833$.

## Step 8
Rounding to a reasonable number of significant figures, $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right) \approx 0.255$.

The final answer is 0.255.
