## Step 4
Applying Chebyshev's inequality to $Y/n$, we have $P(|Y/n - 0.25| \geq 0.05) \leq \frac{Var(Y/n)}{0.05^2} = \frac{0.1875}{n \times 0.05^2}$. Therefore, $P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05) \geq 1 - \frac{0.1875}{n \times 0.05^2}$.

## Step 5
For $n = 500$, we substitute $n$ into our formula to get $P(|Y/n - 0.25| < 0.05) \geq 1 - \frac{0.1875}{500 \times 0.05^2}$.

