To solve $\int_{0}^{1} cx^3(1-x)^6 dx = 1$, we first evaluate the integral $\int_{0}^{1} x^3(1-x)^6 dx$. This is a beta function integral, where $\int_{0}^{1} x^{m-1}(1-x)^{n-1} dx = B(m, n) = \frac{\Gamma(m)\Gamma(n)}{\Gamma(m+n)}$. Here, $m = 4$ and $n = 7$, so the integral becomes $B(4, 7) = \frac{\Gamma(4)\Gamma(7)}{\Gamma(4+7)} = \frac{\Gamma(4)\Gamma(7)}{\Gamma(11)}$.

## Step 4
Calculating the gamma values: $\Gamma(4) = 3! = 6$, $\Gamma(7) = 6! = 720$, and $\Gamma(11) = 10! = 3628800$. So, $B(4, 7) = \frac{6 \times 720}{3628800} = \frac{4320}{3628800}$.

