First, let's use the fact that $P(T' \cap C') = 0.08$ to find $P(T \cup C)$. Since $P(T \cup C) + P(T' \cap C') = 1$, we have $P(T \cup C) = 1 - P(T' \cap C') = 1 - 0.08 = 0.92$.

## Step 4
Using the inclusion-exclusion principle, $P(T \cup C) = P(T) + P(C) - P(T \cap C)$. So, $0.92 = P(T) + P(C) - 0.28$, which simplifies to $P(T) + P(C) = 1.20$.

## Step 5
Substituting $P(T) = P(C) + 0.16$ into $P(T) + P(C) = 1.20$, we get $P(C) + 0.16 + P(C) = 1.20$. Simplifying this gives $2P(C) + 0.16 = 1.20$.

## Step 6
Solving for $P(C)$, we have $2P(C) = 1.20 - 0.16 = 1.04$, so $P(C) = 1.04 / 2 = 0.52$.

## Step 7
Now, we can find $P(T)$ using $P(T) = P(C) + 0.16 = 0.52 + 0.16 = 0.68$.

